ter, he identifies a hopeful path toward wise long-range water-energy decisions and a more reliable and abundant future for humanity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEnergy development. 0aPower resources. 0aRenewable energy sources. 0aWater resources developmentxEnvironmental aspects. 0aWater-power. 0aWater-supplyxManagement. 7aSCIENCE / Environmental Science (see also Chemistry / Environmental).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066771440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030022106040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300221060423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300221060/original  a978-3-11-066771-4  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles